{"format":"tiptap/v1","updatedAt":"2026-06-20T17:50:07.610Z","doc":{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Prefilling"},{"type":"text","text":" (also called "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"speaking for Claude\""},{"type":"text","text":") is a technique where you provide the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"initial part of Claude's response"},{"type":"text","text":", effectively putting words in Claude's mouth that it will then continue from."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Think of it as "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"priming the AI with a starting point"},{"type":"text","text":", which can significantly improve response coherence and relevance."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"What Prefilling Is"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Prefilling"},{"type":"text","text":" is a technique where you provide the model with some initial text to guide its completion. This can be useful if you want the answer to follow a "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"specific format or structure"},{"type":"text","text":", or if you want to "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"speak on behalf of the model"},{"type":"text","text":" to give it some hints about what you want it to say."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Technical implementation:"},{"type":"text","text":" The prefill functionality is implemented with an added "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"prefill"},{"type":"text","text":" parameter that includes the prefill text as an "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"assistant message"},{"type":"text","text":" in the messages array, making Claude continue as if it had already started responding with that text."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Why Prefilling Works"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"1. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Gains Stronger Control Over Format"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Prefilling gives you "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"more control over Claude's response pattern"},{"type":"text","text":" by providing the initial part of its response."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Instead of Claude deciding how to start, you "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"dictate the opening"},{"type":"text","text":", and it continues from there."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"2. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Ensures Consistency"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Prefilling Claude's response helps preserve its role-based behavior"},{"type":"text","text":", ensuring it stays within predefined characters (e.g., helpful assistant or expert advisor)."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"By doing so, you can "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"ensure consistency"},{"type":"text","text":" and maintain the character of Claude's role across interactions."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"3. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Aligns Output with Goals"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"By doing so, users can ensure consistency, maintain the character of Claude's role, and align the output with specific goals or constraints."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"4. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Prevents Fluff"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"You can use prefill with the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"assistant role to prefill the model's answer with an exact list format"},{"type":"text","text":" that you want. This will also "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"prevent the model from generating any \"fluff\" before the list"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Without prefill:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here's the list of top 3 items you requested:\n\n1. Item 1\n2. Item 2\n3. Item 3"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"With prefill:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"1. Item 1\n2. Item 2\n3. Item 3"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"No fluff — just the list."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Prefill Patterns & Effects"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Prefill Pattern"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Effect"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Use Case"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"},{"type":"code"}],"text":"<tag>"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Forces Claude to continue within XML structure"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Creating parseable responses"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"},{"type":"code"}],"text":"{"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Encourages Claude to produce valid JSON"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Generating structured data"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Text snippets"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sets tone or style for continuation"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Controlling response style"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Opening statements"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Guides Claude toward desired content"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Influencing response direction"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"How to Use Prefilling"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Method 1: "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"XML Tag Prefill"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"By prefilling the opening tag, Claude continues directly with the content, ensuring a clean format."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Example:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"xml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Prompt:\n<instructions>\nSummarize this document.\n</instructions>\n\n<input>\n[paste document]\n</input>\n\n<prefill>\n<summary>\n</prefill>"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Claude's output:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"<summary>\nThis document discusses the key findings about...\n</summary>"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Instead of Claude starting with \"Here's the summary:\", you "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"prefill the opening "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"},{"type":"code"}],"text":"<summary>"},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":" tag"},{"type":"text","text":", and it continues directly with the content."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Method 2: "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"JSON Prefill"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"},{"type":"code"}],"text":"{"},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":" encourages Claude to produce valid JSON"},{"type":"text","text":" for generating structured data."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Example:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"json"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Prompt:\nExtract the name, email, and phone from this text.\n\n<input>\n\"Hi, I'm John Smith. You can reach me at john@example.com or 555-1234.\"\n</input>\n\n<prefill>\n{\n</prefill>"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Claude's output:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"json"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"name\": \"John Smith\",\n  \"email\": \"john@example.com\",\n  \"phone\": \"555-1234\"\n}"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The prefill "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"{"},{"type":"text","text":" encourages Claude to produce valid JSON."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Method 3: "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Opening Statement Prefill"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Prefilling can be used to subtly influence Claude's response content without explicitly stating the desired content in the main prompt."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Example:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Prompt:\nWrite a follow-up email after a sales call.\n\n<prefill>\nHi Sarah,\n</prefill>"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Claude's output:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Hi Sarah,\n\nThank you for taking the time to speak with me yesterday. I enjoyed learning about your goals..."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"You "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"prefill the opening \"Hi Sarah,\""},{"type":"text","text":" and Claude continues from there."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Method 4: "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"List Format Prefill"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Use prefill with the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"assistant role to prefill the model's answer with an exact list format"},{"type":"text","text":" that you want."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Example:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Prompt:\nList the top 3 benefits of containerization.\n\n<prefill>\n1.\n</prefill>"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Claude's output:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"1. Deployment speed — packages app + dependencies\n2. Consistency — same environment everywhere\n3. Resource utilization — lightweight, efficient"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"No fluff — just the numbered list."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Method 5: "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Combined Prefill + XML + Stop Sequences"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"When using the Anthropic API directly, you can use the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"},{"type":"code"}],"text":"stop_sequences"},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":" parameter to have Claude stop generating text once it produces certain strings, such as closing XML tags."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Example:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Prompt:\nWrite a haiku about programming.\n\n<prefill>\n<haiku>\n</prefill>\n\n<stop_sequences>\n[\"</haiku>\"]\n</stop_sequences>"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Claude's output:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"xml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"<haiku>\nLines of code flow clean,\nLogic builds the digital world,\nSilent servers hum.\n</haiku>"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Claude stops "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"immediately after generating "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"},{"type":"code"}],"text":"</haiku>"},{"type":"text","text":", saving tokens and reducing irrelevant content."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Real-World Examples"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Example 1: "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Structured Response with XML"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"xml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Prompt:\nAnalyze this code and provide feedback.\n\n<input>\n[paste code]\n</input>\n\n<output_format>\nProvide feedback in this format:\n## Strengths\n## Issues\n## Suggestions\n</output_format>\n\n<prefill>\n## Strengths\n</prefill>"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Claude's output:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Strengths\n- Clean function naming\n- Good error handling\n\n## Issues\n- Missing type annotations\n- No unit tests\n\n## Suggestions\n- Add type hints\n- Write test cases"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Example 2: "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"JSON Data Extraction"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"json"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Prompt:\nExtract product details from this text.\n\n<input>\n\"We sell iPhone 15 Pro for $999 and MacBook Air for $1199.\"\n</input>\n\n<output_format>\nReturn JSON with fields: product, price\n</output_format>\n\n<prefill>\n[\n  {\n    \"product\": \"iPhone 15 Pro\",\n    \"price\": 999\n  },\n  {\n    \"product\": \"MacBook Air\",\n    \"price\": 1199\n  }\n]\n</prefill>"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Note:"},{"type":"text","text":" In this case, you're providing the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"full expected output"},{"type":"text","text":" as prefill. Claude will continue from there, but since it's already complete, it might just echo it back or add minor variations."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Example 3: "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Controlled Tone"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Prompt:\nWrite a rejection email for a job applicant.\n\n<prefill>\nThank you for taking the time to interview for our Senior Developer position.\n</prefill>"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Claude's output:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Thank you for taking the time to interview for our Senior Developer position.\n\nWe were impressed with your technical skills and experience. However, we've decided to move forward with another candidate whose background more closely aligns with our current needs.\n\nWe'll keep your information on file for future opportunities.\n\nBest regards,\nHiring Team"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The prefill sets the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"tone"},{"type":"text","text":" (professional but kind) and "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"direction"},{"type":"text","text":" of the email."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Best Practices for Prefilling"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"1. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Be Specific About Format"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Prefilling gives you more control over Claude's response pattern by providing the initial part of its response."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Use precise opening tags like "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"<summary>"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"{"},{"type":"text","text":", or "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"## Section"},{"type":"text","text":" to dictate the exact format."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"2. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Combine with XML Tags"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"XML tags provide a clear way to delineate different parts of Claude's response, making it easier to extract specific information programmatically."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Combine prefill with XML tags for maximum structure:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"xml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"<prefill>\n<analysis>\n</prefill>"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"3. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Use Stop Sequences"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"When using the Anthropic API directly, you can use the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"},{"type":"code"}],"text":"stop_sequences"},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":" parameter to have Claude stop generating text once it produces certain strings, such as closing XML tags."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This saves tokens and reduces irrelevant content."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"4. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Test Different Prefill Text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Prefilling can be used to subtly influence Claude's response content without explicitly stating the desired content in the main prompt."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Test different opening statements to see which produces the best results."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"5. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Maintain Role Consistency"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Prefilling Claude's responses helps preserve its role-based behavior"},{"type":"text","text":", ensuring it stays within predefined characters."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Use prefill to reinforce the role you've assigned."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Summary"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Prefilling"},{"type":"text","text":" (also called \"speaking for Claude\") is a technique where you provide the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"initial part of Claude's response"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"What it does:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Gains stronger control over format"},{"type":"text","text":" — Dictate the opening structure\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Ensures consistency"},{"type":"text","text":" — Preserve role-based behavior\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Aligns output with goals"},{"type":"text","text":" — Meet specific requirements\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Prevents fluff"},{"type":"text","text":" — No extra text before the content"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Prefill patterns:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n1. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"},{"type":"code"}],"text":"<tag>"},{"type":"text","text":" — Forces XML structure for parseable responses\n2. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"},{"type":"code"}],"text":"{"},{"type":"text","text":" — Encourages valid JSON for structured data\n3. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Text snippets"},{"type":"text","text":" — Sets tone/style for continuation\n4. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Opening statements"},{"type":"text","text":" — Guides toward desired content"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"How to use:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n1. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"XML tag prefill"},{"type":"text","text":" — "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"<summary>"},{"type":"text","text":" to ensure clean format\n2. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"JSON prefill"},{"type":"text","text":" — "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"{"},{"type":"text","text":" for valid JSON output\n3. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Opening statement prefill"},{"type":"text","text":" — \"Hi Sarah,\" to set tone\n4. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"List format prefill"},{"type":"text","text":" — "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"1."},{"type":"text","text":" to prevent fluff\n5. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Combined prefill + stop sequences"},{"type":"text","text":" — "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"code"}],"text":"</haiku>"},{"type":"text","text":" to save tokens"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Best practices:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n1. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Be specific"},{"type":"text","text":" — Use precise opening tags\n2. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Combine with XML"},{"type":"text","text":" — Maximum structure\n3. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Use stop sequences"},{"type":"text","text":" — Save tokens\n4. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Test different text"},{"type":"text","text":" — Find best results\n5. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Maintain consistency"},{"type":"text","text":" — Reinforce role"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Prefilling is super powerful for getting structured, parseable responses from Claude and gaining stronger control over the format and style of Claude's output."}]}]}}
